The paper discusses a parameter learning method for high dimensional density models, which is a common topic in machine learning. The paper also discusses an extension of the method to models of discrete data, which suggests a focus on discrete data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the robustness of the method with noisy training data, which suggests a focus on statistical analysis, making cs.ST (Statistics) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper discusses the link between maximum likelihood and score matching, which suggests a focus on information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category.
